Nelson Rolihlahla Mandela died four years ago on December 5 2013. He passed away at the age of 95 after battling a recurring lung infection. Mandela was elected as South Africa's first democratically elected head of state on May 10 1994. He stepped down in 1999 after one term as president. Take a look at his life and times of the late Nelson Mandela. 

            

